<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2166] Inconsistent/wrong treatment of timestamp parameters in the old Thrift API</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2166</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The old Thrift API treats timestamps wrong/inconsistent.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;getRowTs should return a specific version or null if that doesn&apos;t exist. Currently it does seem to treat the timestamp as exclusive so the row is not found. Same goes for getVerTs but there it might only be a documentation problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll go through the old API and will try to find any such problems and correct them in a way that is consistent with the Java API where possible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter Falk reported this on the mailing list. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
