                            <comment id="13001073" author="stack" created="Tue, 1 Mar 2011 19:56:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This just came up again on the list, Usman Waheed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13968447" author="gunny88" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2014 15:45:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I use thrift 0.9.1.&lt;br/&gt;
When i put data into database (mutateRowTs), i use a number for the timestamp.&lt;br/&gt;
Reading data from database with a number as timestamp woudn&apos;t find any data.&lt;br/&gt;
I found a awful workaroud .... I use a string as timestring and it works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;mutateRowTs (&apos;tab&apos;, &apos;key&apos;, 1234567890 ...)&lt;br/&gt;
getRowTs  (&apos;tab&apos;, &apos;key&apos;, &apos;1234567890&apos; ...)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13969430" author="gunny88" created="Tue, 15 Apr 2014 10:56:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;getRowTs (&apos;tab&apos;, &apos;key&apos;, &apos;1234567890&apos; ...) with string as timestampt treats timestamp as not set and works as getRow(..)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
